# Keep the build context small and, more importantly, HONEST.
#
# Without this, `COPY apps/api ./apps/api` drags in whatever is on the developer's
# machine: a stale `dist/`, and node_modules containing NATIVE binaries built for
# their OS. A Prisma query engine compiled for Windows, copied into an Alpine
# container, fails at runtime with an error that looks like a Prisma bug rather than
# a packaging one. The container must build from source, every time.

node_modules
**/node_modules

dist
**/dist
.next
**/.next
build
coverage
*.tsbuildinfo

.env
.env.*
!.env.example

.git
.github
.vscode
.idea

uploads
scripts/demo
docs
*.md
!README.md

Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
